world.bentobox.bentobox.api.configuration

Interface WorldSettings

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigObject, DataObject

    public interface WorldSettings
extends ConfigObject
    Contains world-specific settings that must be provided by the GameModeAddon in order to register its Worlds.
    Depending on your implementation, you may need to add setters.
    Author:
    tastybento

      @NonNull List<String> getOnJoinCommands()
      Returns a list of commands that should be executed when the player joins an island or creates one.
      These commands are executed by the console, unless otherwise stated using the [SUDO] prefix, in which case they are executed by the player.

      Available placeholders for the commands are the following: [player]: name of the player
      Here are some examples of valid commands to execute: "[SUDO] bbox version" "bsbadmin deaths set [player] 0"
      @NonNull List<String> getOnLeaveCommands()
      Returns a list of commands that should be executed when the player leaves an island or resets one.
      These commands are executed by the console, unless otherwise stated using the [SUDO] prefix, in which case they are executed by the player.

      Available placeholders for the commands are the following: [player]: name of the player
      Here are some examples of valid commands to execute: "[SUDO] bbox version" "bsbadmin deaths set [player] 0"
      Note that player-executed commands might not work, as these commands can be run with said player being offline.

      • getOnJoinCommands

        @NonNull List<String> getOnJoinCommands()
        Returns a list of commands that should be executed when the player joins an island or creates one.
        These commands are executed by the console, unless otherwise stated using the [SUDO] prefix, in which case they are executed by the player.

        Available placeholders for the commands are the following:
        • [player]: name of the player

        Here are some examples of valid commands to execute:
        • "[SUDO] bbox version"
        • "bsbadmin deaths set [player] 0"
        Returns:
        a list of commands.
        Since:
        1.8.0
        See Also:
        getOnLeaveCommands()

      • getOnLeaveCommands

        @NonNull List<String> getOnLeaveCommands()
        Returns a list of commands that should be executed when the player leaves an island or resets one.
        These commands are executed by the console, unless otherwise stated using the [SUDO] prefix, in which case they are executed by the player.

        Available placeholders for the commands are the following:
        • [player]: name of the player

        Here are some examples of valid commands to execute:
        • "[SUDO] bbox version"
        • "bsbadmin deaths set [player] 0"

        Note that player-executed commands might not work, as these commands can be run with said player being offline.
        Returns:
        a list of commands.
        Since:
        1.8.0
        See Also:
        getOnJoinCommands()
